cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper discusses a new perspective on multi-class learning algorithms, specifically one-vs-all and output-codes. These algorithms are commonly used in machine learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the geometry of the output code, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper provides results for learning linear classifiers, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
